  "texts": [
    "In addition, data sets such as COLLAB (Yanardag and Vishwanathan 2015), IMDB-BINARY (Yanardag and Vishwanathan 2015) and IMDB-MULTI (Yanardag and Vishwanathan 2015) focus on social network data.",
    "These data sets include graph data such as scientific collaboration networks and film collaboration networks, providing rich experimental materials for social network analysis.",
    "However, due to the relatively small size of the datasets in TUDatasets, this may lead to model design bias toward specific, small-scale graph structures when evaluating new methods, and may reduce the reproducibility and generalization ability of experimental results.",
    "To address this challenge, Benchmarking GNNs proposes a series of new, mid-scale datasets that cover a wide range of domains such as chemistry, mathematical modeling, computer vision, combinatorial optimization, and social networks, aiming at more accurately modeling complex graph structures in the real world.",
    "For example, the ZINC (Dwivedi et al. 2023) dataset is a graph regression task dataset in the field of chemistry, which contains a large number of organic molecule graphs and their related physical or chemical properties."
